    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I would argue the current behavior is the correct behavior. It is consistent with the way ```str.split()``` works in core python.\r\n\r\n```\r\n>>> ''.split()\r\n[]\r\n>>> 'a'.split()\r\n['a']\r\n>>> 'a b'.split()\r\n['a', 'b']\r\n>>> pd.Series(['', 'a', 'a b']).str.split(expand=True)\r\n      0     1\r\n0  None  None\r\n1     a  None\r\n2     a     b\r\n```\r\n\r\nand thus the current behavior makes a lot of sense\r\n\r\n```\r\n>>> pandas.DataFrame({'test': ['']}).test.str.split(expand=True)\r\nEmpty DataFrame\r\nColumns: []\r\nIndex: [0]\r\n```"
  },
